properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 18 at 8:58PM CST until January 19 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Mobile AL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog.

* WHERE...Baldwin Central and Baldwin Coastal Counties.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A light southeasterly flow just out in
advance of an approaching cold front is advecting warm and moist
air over the much cooler waters of Mobile Bay, Mississippi Sound
and the near shore Gulf waters. As a result areas of fog, dense
in some locations, has developed. This will likely persist
through this evening, but by midnight the front will be moving
through the area and a drier more west to northwesterly wind
flow will develop and the fog should begin to dissipate.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST TONIGHT
